WEBVTT

00:00.600 --> 00:02.190
My name is Michael Westen.

00:02.200 --> 00:04.700
I used to be a spy until...

00:04.730 --> 00:07.850
We got a burn notice on you. You're blacklisted.

00:07.880 --> 00:12.680
When you're burned, you've got nothing... 
no cash, no credit, no job history.

00:12.720 --> 00:15.010
You're stuck in whatever city
they decide to dump you in.

00:15.050 --> 00:17.040
Where am I?
Miami.

00:17.180 --> 00:20.080
You do whatever work comes your way.

00:20.090 --> 00:23.380
You rely on anyone who's still talking to you.

00:23.410 --> 00:24.830
A trigger-happy ex-girlfriend...

00:24.840 --> 00:26.030
Should we shoot them?

00:26.040 --> 00:28.600
An old friend who used to inform on you to the FBI...

00:28.610 --> 00:31.300
You know spies... a bunch of bitchy little girls.

00:31.310 --> 00:32.060
Family, too...

00:32.070 --> 00:33.240
Hey, is that your mom again?

00:33.250 --> 00:34.500
If you're desperate.

00:34.510 --> 00:36.060
Someone needs your help, Michael.

00:36.070 --> 00:40.830
Bottom line... as long as you're
burned, you're not going anywhere.

00:42.000 --> 00:48.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:54.340 --> 00:56.700
Spies aren't much into nightclubs.

00:56.710 --> 00:59.960
In a career where hearing loss
is a serious operational concern

00:59.970 --> 01:02.830
and crowds of strangers have
to be constantly monitored, 

01:02.840 --> 01:05.680
they just don't seem like much fun.

01:05.690 --> 01:08.730
I'm just saying you live above
the club. Aren't you curious?

01:08.740 --> 01:10.000
You can hear the music through the floor.

01:10.010 --> 01:12.420
Sam's got beer in the fridge. Knock yourself out.

01:12.430 --> 01:13.900
We're just back there.

01:13.940 --> 01:17.460
You know, it's not the same when no one's watching.

01:21.080 --> 01:23.390
Uh, the line to the club's out there.

01:23.400 --> 01:25.020
I'm here for you.

01:25.030 --> 01:25.830
Excuse me?

01:25.840 --> 01:28.060
Excuse me.

01:28.520 --> 01:30.000
This is for you.

01:30.010 --> 01:32.370
It's rejuvenating body lotion.

01:32.380 --> 01:34.400
A gift from a friend.

01:34.410 --> 01:36.510
I can apply itif you'd like.

01:36.520 --> 01:39.200
That won't be necessary.

01:40.890 --> 01:44.230
Who's this friend giving you rejuvenating body lotion?

01:44.240 --> 01:45.230
He's not a friend.

01:45.240 --> 01:46.560
He's a recruiter.

01:46.570 --> 01:48.330
Oh, Strickler.

01:48.650 --> 01:51.020
I can apply it if you want.

01:52.430 --> 01:57.110
Training a covert operative takes
years and costs a lot of money.

01:57.120 --> 02:00.890
In theory, it's all for the taxpayers who pay the bills.

02:00.900 --> 02:03.990
In practice, it's worth a lot on the open market.

02:04.000 --> 02:08.580
And when something's that valuable,
there's always someone trying to sell it.

02:08.590 --> 02:10.720
Oh, you didn't like the lotion.

02:14.030 --> 02:16.000
It's organic. Best money can buy.

02:16.010 --> 02:18.200
You know, I'm all set with lotion right now.

02:18.210 --> 02:20.730
Like I told you before, I'm not interested in your money.

02:20.740 --> 02:21.920
This isn't about money.

02:21.930 --> 02:23.320
Did you even look at the lotion?

02:23.330 --> 02:26.750
It's 40% aloe vera. They say it's great for burns.

02:26.760 --> 02:28.620
Want a mimosa?

02:29.490 --> 02:32.860
So, uh, it's all about the burn notice with you, isn't it?

02:32.870 --> 02:35.320
Well, I might be able to help out with that.

02:35.330 --> 02:37.560
How's that? With moisturizer?

02:38.410 --> 02:44.550
Remember that NSA logistics guy who got caught up
in the Panamanian banking scandal a couple years back?

02:45.310 --> 02:46.960
Rings a bell.

02:46.980 --> 02:49.020
Should have ended his career.

02:49.050 --> 02:54.300
But he had a second chance because of a conversation
he had with the right person on a ski lift in Aspen.

02:54.310 --> 02:55.710
I know, 'cause I was there.

02:55.720 --> 02:58.270
If we were working together, I'd be there for you, too.

02:58.280 --> 02:59.860
As your mercenary?

02:59.870 --> 03:01.260
No, I'm not interested.

03:01.270 --> 03:03.100
As a friend.

03:03.110 --> 03:05.660
Friends do each other favors.

03:05.710 --> 03:08.930
Listen, Michael, we all know what's
at the top of your Christmas list.

03:08.940 --> 03:13.550
Work with me, I can deliver that list to Santa himself.

03:17.880 --> 03:20.290
Spies hate drop-in visits.

03:20.300 --> 03:24.100
Any questionable contact has
to be reported to superiors.

03:24.110 --> 03:28.530
A process that involves hours of
paperwork and uncomfortable questions.

03:29.360 --> 03:33.080
If you're a questionable contact,
that gives you some leverage.

03:33.090 --> 03:38.410
If you know where a spy operates, even a guy
running a lowly import/export cover business...

03:38.420 --> 03:39.740
Diego!

03:39.750 --> 03:41.800
You can make someone's life miserable.

03:41.810 --> 03:42.680
What are you doing here?

03:42.690 --> 03:47.420
What? I can't just drop by and say
hi to my favorite "point of contact"?

03:50.170 --> 03:51.640
I thought it was clear last time we spoke, 

03:51.650 --> 03:55.430
if anyone from the intelligence community
has anything to share, I'll call you.

03:55.440 --> 03:56.890
I know, I know, I know. I need a favor.

03:56.900 --> 03:59.280
I'm already doing you a favor by not calling the police.

03:59.290 --> 04:00.390
Another favor, then.

04:00.400 --> 04:03.680
There's a name I need you to
check out... Tom Strickler.

04:03.690 --> 04:05.810
He offered to help out with this whole burn notice thing.

04:05.820 --> 04:08.280
I need you to find out if he's
a guy who can make things happen.

04:08.290 --> 04:10.260
Maybe you should Google him...

04:10.270 --> 04:12.830
or go find someone who cares.

04:13.990 --> 04:15.420
See? Now you have to care.

04:15.430 --> 04:20.790
I let the local Homeland Security office know that
I was dropping by and leaving that document there.

04:20.800 --> 04:22.900
I'll check in later.

04:28.850 --> 04:30.720
You don't even know this Strickler.

04:30.730 --> 04:32.290
What makes you think he has this kind of clout?

04:32.300 --> 04:33.820
Well, that's what I need to figure out.

04:33.830 --> 04:35.370
Can we talk about something else?

04:35.380 --> 04:37.420
No. I'm cooking at my place.

04:37.430 --> 04:41.030
I get to choose the topic of conversation.

04:41.040 --> 04:44.110
You seriously think he's gonna wave
his magic spy wand and get you back in?

04:44.120 --> 04:45.680
It's a little more complicated than that, Fi.

04:45.720 --> 04:49.190
Well, in my experience, if something seems too good
to be true, it's best to shoot it, just in case.

04:49.200 --> 04:50.800
One way or another, I need to check him out.

04:50.810 --> 04:53.380
If he's half as connected as he claimed, I need to know.

04:53.390 --> 04:54.930
You're not actually considering his offer?

04:54.940 --> 04:56.530
Michael, the guy is sleazy... 
Fi.

04:56.540 --> 04:58.560
Don't change the subject. I want to know... 

04:58.570 --> 05:01.250
Were you expecting a guest?

05:03.950 --> 05:08.970
If you want to stay alive, you have to be
able to recognize the signs of a break-in.

05:10.940 --> 05:18.900
The most skilled operative in the world won't last long
if he walks into an ambush carrying a box of cereal.

05:21.460 --> 05:26.280
When a target is cornered, the best strategy
is to flush them into a choke point, 

05:26.290 --> 05:29.720
where they have two options... surrender, or be shot.

05:29.730 --> 05:31.170
Drop it!

05:31.180 --> 05:36.400
Of course, if your target turns out to be
13 years old carrying a dismantled pistol, 

05:36.410 --> 05:39.860
it changes the tactical response somewhat.

06:02.320 --> 06:05.060
Hey, all right.

06:05.900 --> 06:07.500
Easy, easy, easy, easy.

06:07.510 --> 06:10.280
Look, man, I'm sorry! I was
just gonna borrow it, I swear!

06:10.300 --> 06:12.610
Yeah, you "borrow"a cup of sugar.
You don't borrow a gun.

06:12.620 --> 06:13.800
I'm sorry. I'm gonna have to call your parents.

06:13.810 --> 06:15.370
You don't understand, man! I have to... 

06:15.420 --> 06:16.840
You have to what?

06:16.850 --> 06:18.830
Look, just... just let me go, man.

06:18.840 --> 06:21.940
I will when you answer me.

06:21.950 --> 06:24.870
I... I have to kill my stepdad.

